sts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 9:44:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2211.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Roleplay as a Troll or Ogre</span><hr size=1> I find myself sometimes missing the roleplay that occurs among the other races. I just don't find it fulfilling to always type as a dumb troll, and that be the extent of my roleplay...<br>
<br>
Perhaps I'm just not creative, so I'd like to ask any ogres or trolls if they've come up with ways to interact and roleplay even though most races are either afraid of us, food for us, want to kill us, or think we're too stupid to waste time on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uburanmcmuffin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BuranMcMuffin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 10:07:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2211.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplay as a Troll or Ogre</span><hr size=1> ooc: I RPed an Ogre shaman on another server who was brilliant but for the most part mute. I used emotes as my primary means of communication and spoke very very rarely...<br>
<br>
 *smiles* It was always entertaining to see people's reactions when I would remain quiet for the most part, and then when someone would ask something like &quot;Which would be better for me to use as an SK, a Noc Blade or Sword of Skyfire?&quot; and I would emote something like:<br>
<br>
Ignoxious knows Skyfire has a AoE fire proc at higher levels, which adds damage but also breaks mez.<br>
<br>
Ignoxious also knows the Noc Blade has +15 Int, which will convert to a solid increase in mana, and also weighs very little, so it wont be taxing to wield.<br>
<br>
Ignoxious is acutely aware that the 1.44 ratio on the Noc Blade is superior to the 2.20 ratio on the Skyfire, but is also aware of the 5k to 6k difference in prices on the open market.<br>
<br>
Ignoxious sighs quietly, says nothing, and goes back to reading &quot;How to Liquidate Starlight: A Celestial Guide to Making Potions that Matter.&quot;<br>
<br>
You can have fun with anything if you pick a random direction and think it through far enough.<br>
<br>
Buran McMuffin, the original Iron Chef<br>
**Slayin gnolls n makin muffins since 3174**<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 11:49:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2211.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplay as a Troll or Ogre</span><hr size=1> You don't need to play a dumb troll.  You could play a troll with a speech impediment, but say things with absolutely incredible meaning behind them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/29/02 5:29:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2211.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not all trolls are stupid...</span><hr size=1> ...but the smart ones tend ta be incredibly cunning,evil,an' cruel.<br>
<br>
Xicotl was a smart one. Wouldn't be a Freeport knight's guild without him an' Pietro havin' made it.<br>
 <br>
-Morgrist<br>
