<br>
I play Krazak with the full vocabulary that I have. I play Krazak as a smart Ogre, because Krazak likes to think he's better than everyone else. Krazak is a deciple of Cazic Thule, unlike most Ogres who worship Ralloz The Wenie-Zek. Krazak thinks that Cazic Thule is the greatest of the Gods, and so he concludes that if he's a direct deciple of the greatest God, he must be great himself. (Yeah, he's kinda stuck up)<br>
<br>
Anyway... back to the vocabulary. I don't think you need much of a roleplay reason to speak intelligently. There was a time when I played a Troll SK on this server, and did the same thing. I concocted a story about him being aided by an Erudite SK, and taught how to speak in a more intelligent manner... <br>
<br>
There's a lot of possibilities. Surprise yourself! And then surprise others with your smart troll or ogre!<br>
<br>
-Krazak Thule<br>
-Keeping down the gnome population, one meal at a time <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=grumgor>Grumgor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:07:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2211.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trolls and Ogers</span><hr size=1> Indeed, I've re-evaluated my manner of speaking.<br>
